Glob patterns + |variant syntax - NOT just targets, also PROPERTY TESTING!

Variant use cases:
1. Target-specific: |gpu, |cpu, |wasm, |js
2. Implementation variants: |zig(reference), |zig(optimized)
3. Property testing: verify optimized == reference for random inputs

Syntax:
- ~proc event|target              (gpu, wasm, js)
- ~proc event|target(qualifier)   (zig(reference), zig(optimized))
- ~proc event.*|variant           (glob + variant)

Property testing pattern:
- Write simple reference impl (obviously correct)
- Write optimized impl (fast but complex)
- Test: for random inputs, both produce same output
- Confidence that optimization didn't break correctness

Combined with globs:
- ~proc transform.*|zig(reference) - reference for ALL transforms
- ~proc transform.*|zig(optimized) - optimized for ALL transforms
- Property test the entire family at once!
